    description: '<p>The web of water bodies suggests an intimate knowledge of the landscape. Along the gradient of the Chidia toonk hill, the seepage route was traced through rock ﬁssures to dig wells and step-wells strategically. </p><p>Gradient of the city in terms of water bodies was placed thus: Ranisar to Padamsar to Chand Bawdi to Jaita Bera to Joshiyon ka kuan and further. These water bodies in Brahmpuri are a site of ritual, conversation, festivities and the sundry.</p>'
