    title: 1. Padmasar Lake
    description: '<p>Padamsar lake, the twin lake attached to Ranisar, was built in the 16th century. Contesting narratives claim Rani Padam Devadi or Baldia Seth to be its sponsors. It was donated to the Srimali Brahmins residing in Brahmpuri adjoining the lake.</p><p>Today, the lake is the site of many rituals, including Diwali, the festival of lights as well as Tarpan, the ceremony for ancestors.</p><p>- Connected lake to Ranisar. -Origin and history of this lake<br>- Which community uses it.  -Use in Festivities across years.</p>'
